-- ABB, Lundbeck, Opera Software, Stora Enso, Yara: Nordic Stock Preview
-- Adam Ewing
-- 2010-06-15T06:18:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/abb-lundbeck-opera-software-stora-enso-yara-nordic-stock-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Nordic trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are from the previous close.  
 The  Stoxx Nordic 30 Index , a measure for the region, rose
113.24, or 1.7 percent, to 6,618.61.  
 The  OMX Stockholm 30 Index  increased 1.6 percent as the
 Helsinki 25 Index  added 2 percent. The  Copenhagen 20 Index 
climbed 2.1 percent. Norway’s  OBX Index  climbed 2.8 percent.  
 ABB Ltd.  (ABB SS): The world’s largest builder of power-
transmission networks was raised to “overweight” from
“equalweight” at Morgan Stanley. The shares rose 2.3 percent
to 142.6 kronor.  
 H. Lundbeck A/S  (LUN DC): The Nordic region’s second-
largest drugmaker will get a bigger share of revenue from
international markets going forward as its Cipralex drug gains
share in Canada and Japan, the Copenhagen-based Dagbladet Borsen
newspaper reported, citing  Ole Chrintz , an executive at
Lundbeck. The shares increased 0.6 percent to 88.3 kroner.  
 Opera Software ASA  (OPERA NO): The Norwegian maker of Web
browsers for desktop and portable devices plans to double its
mobile and computer subscribers in India to 10 million each in
six months, the Economic Times reported, citing Chief Executive
Officer  Lars Boilesen . The shares increased 1.7 percent to 24.4
kroner.  
 Stora Enso Oyj  (STERV FH): Europe’s largest papermaker
started talks to temporarily lay off as many as 500 workers at
Finnish sawmills in response to the threat of uncompetitive wood
cost levels. The shares climbed 5.1 percent to 6.85 euros.  
 TGS Nopec Geophysical Co. ASA  (TGS NO): The Norwegian oil
and gas service provider said its geological products division
purchased the directional survey business of P2 Energy
Solutions’ Tobin business line. The shares jumped 4.5 percent to
83.6 kroner.  
 Yara International ASA  (YAR NO): The world’s largest
supplier of mineral fertilizers was downgraded to “reduce”
from “neutral” at Nomura Holdings Inc. The shares gained 2
percent to 202 kroner.  
